    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ 425\u00b0F/ Gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Chop the<strong> potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuna-nicoise-with-crispy-caper-potatoes/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiling water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook over a high heat for 10-15 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return them to the pot</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuna-nicoise-with-crispy-caper-potatoes/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, reboil a kettle</p><p>Wash and chop the <strong>red gem lettuce </strong>in half\u00a0widthways and discard the stem</p><p>Cut the <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Chop\u00a0the <strong>black olives </strong>roughly</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuna-nicoise-with-crispy-caper-potatoes/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained\u00a0potatoes</strong>\u00a0to a baking tray and crush them gently with a fork</p><p>Sprinkle the <strong>capers</strong> over the<strong> crushed potatoes</strong></p><p>Drizzle everything with <strong>olive oil</strong>, season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a gentle mix up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 15-20 min, or until golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuna-nicoise-with-crispy-caper-potatoes/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, add the <strong>eggs</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiling water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> over a high heat (salt prevents the eggs from cracking!)</p><p>Boil for an initial 4 min</p><p>After 4 min add the <strong>green beans</strong> and boil for a further 3-4 min or until the beans are tender</p><p>Once done, drain and run everything under <strong>cold water</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuna-nicoise-with-crispy-caper-potatoes/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine the<strong> Dijon mustard</strong> and <strong>white wine vinegar</strong> with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> in a large bowl \u2013 this is your <strong>Dijon vinaigrette</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuna-nicoise-with-crispy-caper-potatoes/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped red gem lettuce</strong>, <strong>halved</strong> <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong>, <strong>black olives</strong> and <strong>cooked green beans</strong> to the <strong>Dijon</strong> <strong>vinaigrette</strong>\u00a0and give everything a gentle mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>dressed salad</strong></p><p>Peel the<strong> cooled eggs</strong> and cut them into quarters</p><p>Drain the <strong>canned tuna</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuna-nicoise-with-crispy-caper-potatoes/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Divide the <strong>dressed salad</strong> between your serving bowls and top with the <strong>canned</strong> <strong>tuna</strong> and <strong>egg quarters</strong></p><p>Sprinkle over the <strong>crispy caper potatoes</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
